comment: Daps discusses Judas and the Black Messiah an American biographical drama film about the betrayal of Fred Hampton (Daniel Kaluuya), chairman of the Illinois chapter of the Black Panther Party in late - 1960s Chicago, at the hands of William O'Neal (Lakeith Stanfield), an FBI informant. Oh, and Daps also discusses Chris D'Elia's  it's been a while video!!

comment: In this episode, Daps reflects a bit on life. He discusses making use of time wisely in the last third of Q1 in order to still achieve those goals that we set for ourselves at the start of the year. Of course Daps always finds a way to relate everything to Clubhouse, he loves the app too much. Do you think June 21st should be a national holiday? What are your plans for June 21st??
title: #009 - How are you looking coming up to end of Q1? June 21st!

comment: Great chat with Whoistaf, founder of Sliders Podcast. The podcast runs every week, with four friends who live in - and are experiencing - Newcastle as students. We discuss movies, bad sequels, TikTok challenges and more.

comment: I had the pleasure of sitting down with one of the coolest men I've met in a really long time. Mr G Congo is a man who's been incarcerated, but has massively turned his life around and lives by example. \n\nHis instagram home workout videos are really refreshing and will definitely get you in a positive mindset to start and end your day right. He'll be be running some dance classes at a Sunderland gym once we come out of lockdown, in order to help people find their afro vibe.
title: #011 - Mr G Congo

comment: My friend Tom joins me in the studio. Tom is a Mortgage Protection adviser, he shares some insights into the importance of considering financial protection and how to go about securing a policy for yourself.
title: #012 - Tom Richardson

comment: Daps is back in for another weekend of telling it how it is. He gives us a rundown of what's happened in the last two weeks and what could be coming in the future. He also gives us an interesting perspective on the Derrick Jaxn cheating scandal.
title: #013 - Clubhouse Shenanigans, Derrick Jaxn

comment: Sam Barton is a classic physique bodybuilder in Newcastle, England. He's currently training for the Arnold Classic competition, which will be happening for the first time ever in the UK in October. Sam shares some interesting perspectives on training, motivation and diet.
title: #014 - Sam Barton

comment: Dark Man X has left this world to partake in the next thing whatever that is. He's in a better place. Prince Phillip died at 99 because he couldn't keep it a 100%. Gone too soon!
title: #015 - RIP DMX, Adios Prince Phillip

comment: My reflections after watching prince Philip's funeral service. I felt like it was a poignant performance. It also made me go down a rabbit hole of wondering, What is it that makes us afraid of dying? What makes loosing someone so painful and unbearable?\n
title: #016 - A royal funeral ends in a royal vault.

comment: There are two Nuga Bros! Dami is one of them, and probably the coolest. I had the pleasure of having my brother from our actual mother on my show today. He's a video game developer (environment artist). He's worked on triple A games such as Tom Clancy's The Division 2 and brings a wealth of wisdom, knowledge & experience from the widely coveted video game developer world.
title: #017 - Dami Nuga

O Maya was founded with the intention of catering to everyones hair needs, white or black. A unique brand in their choice of ingredients, social media engagement and interaction. We're excited for O Maya and their future within the beauty & fashion industry.
title: #018 - O Maya Beauty UK

Overall the experience of gigging has been fun but performing in front of an audience has been exhilarating.\n

comment: Mosqiuotos!!! Spanish word for little fly, with species such as the Culex Molestus. I'm pretty convinced that Mosquitos evolved on earth to molest us all, no one is safe! DTP 'Dan The Producer' got absolutely feasted on last week by British Mozzys. Thankfully he's recovering and lives to tell the tale.\n\nI too have suffered from the odd Mosquito bite in the past. Heck, I may even have suffered from malaria at some point. Thank God for Chloroquine and Nigerian nurses and doctors who love the auld butt cheeks. Soon as you rock up to a hospital joint sick with malaria which gets transmitted by infected mosquitos. Your butt cheeks are in for getting an unapologetic jab of the Quine!!
title: #030 - British Mozzys and the Nigerian Molesteria conspiracy

He's a brand specialist to the core, in my opinion.

They're currently performing their Soul & Gospel shows at a few venues around Newcastle, England. Their performance at Hoochie Coochie was a massive success, The Globe is next. The choir promises to end the year with a bang as they plan to put on a final performance at The Cluny on November 7th. Save the date!

comment: TJ Hickey is a singer/songwriter based in Boston, Massachusetts. He has over 50k monthly listeners on Spotify. We discuss his strategy of releasing a new song every Friday in order to give him the best chance of making it onto popular playlists. He truly is a talented and fascinating man.

comment: The Nigerian Yorkshireman giant, representing the north of England in rap and grime. If you don't sweat from vibing like a maniac at his concerts, I'd suggest a visit to your GP to ensure you ain't down with an illness.

Forget what the app says, it's the 50th episode of Positive Energy!

comment:
A full return to the usual format.
 
Stories include: the discovery of galaxy discs, Aldi manager arranging for meals to be sent to an elderly shopper who only bought tinned food, Crayola release multi-ethnicity 'skin coloured' crayons, and a priest using a water gun to perform social-distanced blessings.

Music includes: happy hardcore, drum and bass, old skool, hard trance and techno.  

Note: some explicit lyrics, which are forewarned.
title: Music Discs And Galaxy Discs

comment: Stories of love and light come from times of darkness, and today we find those glimmers of hope arising from the current racial issues in America, and around the world.  Carefully selected music to go along with this, in a variety of genres. From disco to D'n'B, hip-hop to 90s dance.
title: Black Once Again With The Jenegade Master

comment: A celebration of positive progress, following a week of protests and actions involving the BLM movement. Also, nature's way of dealing with plastics. \nStacks of hardcore today, which is GREAT, obviously!
title: Hardcore Progress

title: In The Mood... But Which One?

comment: Even more Positive Energy!  We enjoy quick-fire stories of kindness and blast some upbeat tunes on this fine, hot day. May or may not include your recommended daily intake of humming.
title: Inaugral Friday Fun

comment: We learn about a newly-discovered particle; there are more Native American women in Congress; more penguins than we thought; a toy horse that's making its way around Norfolk. \nAlso, it's very hot. Did I mention that?
title: Shooting Stars

comment: We ride waves of joy through some hardcore tunes and heart-warming stories of everyday humans doing wonderful stuff.  Now with added Smooth Jazz Voice!
title: Super Mega Friday Love Vibes

comment: Animals are rad, we should treat them well.  We hear of how this is actualised around the world, with rehoming, rediscovery, and brave love. Interspersed with old skool, happy hardcore and other random stuff.
title: Elephants, Sharks, Mice and Wonder Woman.

comment: We hear of an amazing feat in the potential reversal of us fucking things up for white rhinos, along with some other stories of extraordinary selflessness.
title: Kind & Dandy

comment: A bit of a strange show, as we talk about suicide. It's not the jolliest subject, but talking is the antidote. \n\nHowever, we also talk nice stuff! New gorillas and dinosaurs, DJing GCSEs, and other random chitchat.

title: Don't You Try To Bring Me Down Now

comment: Listen for mid 00s cheesey favourites. Do not listen for good mixing.  Good news slotted in later.
title: Hardcore, Zero Score

comment: We discover what new jobs DJs can retrain for. There's stories of goodness, kindness, heroism, and a frankly random selection of music.
title: Retrain In The Membrane

comment: Lots of good news, with the usual odd selection of music. We brock out, rock out, rave up and Disney it. Glitter is cancelled (boo/yay), music grants are given (yay), rare racoons, nature reserve plans, marine reserves and more.
title: I'm Still Standing

comment: Cute stories. 90s cheese. Trance. What more do you want... organised shows!?
title: Sunshine After The Rain

comment: ...Where good news is my fantasy :)
title: Take Me Up, Up ,Up And Away...

comment: Two listener birthdays today! Join the celebrations with random tunes, requests, and good news to perk up the mood. \n:)
title: Bits & Pieces

comment: Music changes at every turn! No orangutans were harmed in the making of this nonsense.
title: Every Which Way But Loose

comment: We celebrate the return of Moving Shadow with some classics from the label.  A sprinkling of uplifting stories of human kindness and achievement glues it all together.
title: Grooving Shadow

comment: Tunes inspired by the wonderful Charlie, whom we celebrate today. Good news of human kindness and adorable deeds, dog news, and probably other stuff.
title: Life, It's All About Expression. So Express Yourself, Yeah, Yeah.

comment: A cheery Wednesday boost, filled with tunes and stories of good in the world.
title: Lift Me Up

comment: It's World Kindness Day and we are ALLLLL over it on today's show :)
title: Try A Little Kindness

comment: That time Jen broke live on air.
title: Powerjen.exe Has Stopped Working

comment: The only way is up. Music of this ilk, and lots of dog news today :)
title: Hold Your Head High

comment: Flutter through this Wednesday morning with me, some banging tunes, and cute stories :)
title: Power Montage

comment: Celebrating the outstanding Jimi Hendrix on his birthday with some, turns out, great dance remixes.  Loads of new endangered animals born recently, and humans being nice :)
title: Jeni Hendrix

comment: The show makes about as much sense as the title, which makes more sense upon listening. Enjoyable chaos, apparently.
title: Break My Baked Potato

comment: Elephants, 90s, dancing, penguins, AND MORE!  Obligatory random remix, and music from Kniteforce, Knitebreed, and Threshold.fm's very own Parallaxed.
title: Neverending Non-Exclusives

comment: Delve into some old hardcore tracks, and hear of tiny animals and brilliant humans doing nice things.
title: Fusion Groove On

comment: Bit of a ranty one today, but we get to the cheer by the end.  From gentle breaks and house beginnings to trance and D'n'B.  And maybe Disney, I couldn't possibly say....
title: A Spoonful of D'n'B Helps The Fox Hunt Get Banned

comment: Not quite the show I had in mind as I got some sad news moments before the show, but hear a selection of my favourite tunes across many genres, and hopefully not me crying in the background!
title: It's My Birthday and I'll Cry If I Want To

comment: Joy to the world - Christmas remixes!  Christmassy good news stories to warm your heart, and tunes that will melt your brain
title: It's Beginning to Sound a lot like Christmas...

comment: Such love and kindness has come out this Christmas time. Hear all about it, and tunes from Coco Bryce, The Omen, No Doubt and Reel Big Fish. Sorry about the sound issues!
title: Christmas Kindness & Sketchy Sound

comment: A celebration of the sweetest moments of 2020, as we mosey on into 2021. \n:)
title: Positive Energy Awards 2020

comment: Tips for going back into lockdown. Reports of thriving muskoxen. A man who built a forest, arctic drilling denied, and a Chrome extension to support local shopping. Hardcore, hard trance and D'n'B provide the soundtrack.
title: Muskoxenisationing On Profeshold.fm

comment: Georgia keeps cropping up this episode. Lovely stories and groovy parcels of noise to cheer you up.
title: Georgia, The Whole Show Through

comment: A pretty silly show today, with metal and 8-bit covers of theme tunes, plus a couple of gems of sensible music. Good news includes: cat pen-pals, a generous doctor, and a teacher working extra to buy students Christmas gifts.
title: Why Is Pokemon Stuck In My Head?

comment: A spontaneous show of tracks by - or remixed by - Luna-C. Lovely good news of medical advances and human kindness, plus a bonus 30 minutes of mega tunes!
title: Sheer Luna-C!

comment: Music themed around time today, a selection I very much enjoyed.  Lots of dog news, as well as bears, astronauts, and old people beating Covid-19.
title: IIIIIIIIIIIIN TIYYYME

comment: Back after a brief hiatus, and we've loads of news to cover! Biden, science, kindness, bans of plastic and animals in circuses. Music from Silkcuts 1, Quest, Miss Behaving.
title: Return of the Jen-I

comment: Loads of upfront hardcore today! News of artificial hearts, TikTok helping people living with Parkinson's, wild flower meadows FTW, and an electrician whose simple job turned into a huge project helping old people.
title: Not-So-Simply Electric

comment: Today we explore some of our favourite words, and (albeit sometimes bizarre) tunes with 'word', 'say' etc in. No news stories today as I was distracted by the theme, but there's defo good news out there!
title: Word To Your Mother

comment: Back with good news - animal friends, plastic bricks stronger than concrete, double kind deeds, stolen bikes and power from hills - and a great selection of music about music. A reminder that music is the answer, even within itself.
title: Music About Music

comment: Lush fluffy tunes today, from the worlds of trance, techno house stuff, breaks, drum & bass, and an exclusive play of Mobi-D's new cinematic venture. Good news: tech savvy spinach, senior dog care, child amputee supporting others, clear masks, AND STUFF.
title: Fluff

comment: Good deeds; helping those in the big Texas freeze to warm your heart, Mars Rover lands, skin tone crayons, therapy sphynx cat, and a decline in oil production and poaching. Breakbeat hardcore, hard trance, and some random bits.
title: What Do Sea Turtles And Space X Have In Common?

comment: Not the usual fun and bouncy episode, but its content is important.  We explore ways that we - particularly men - can be there for each other against attacks and bond as fellow humans.
title: Helping Each Other Stay Safe

comment: Return to form with oodles of good news and favourite tracks.
title: Back On Track

comment: Buzz Lightyear toy makes his way home thanks to airport staff, science news, nature news, Right to Repair, and more. Musically, we trundle down memory lane of tunes I've shared with Bendy P, as a farewell gift. Hardcore, lots of hardcore.
title: To Infinity And Beyond

comment: All sorts of random tunes, and lovely stories of medical advances, reforesting drones, care homes and school music programme, and a delightful story of a facebook mix up.
title: Wake(field) Up, Get Out Of Bed

comment: Classic rock, hard house, freeform, D'n'B, happy hardcore, ambient - it's all go musically today! News of bioplastic, fundraising, vaccines, helping Asian-Americans, helping animals, cleaning Everest and MORE!
title: More Than A Feeling

comment: Plastic, electricity, recycling, empathy, diversity, community action - all topics today. Along with a bizarre mix of breakbeat hardcore, D'n'B, Motown, happy hardcore and pop punk!
title: 86'd

comment: Condensed show of goodness and random tunes. Good for your soul and your ears.
title: Brand New Day

comment: Good deeds, helping the homeless, paper beer bottles, justice, rhinos - its all here! Music from Luna-c, Zoe, Force & Styles (and Breeze), Twisted Sister, Jenna G, and Bill Hicks sees us out.
title: A Better World

comment: Peace and love vibes today to mark Earth Day 2021. Good news stories relating to the planet and nature, and music-wise we have drum&bass, 70s hippy rock, and maybe a cheeky Disney track, I couldn't possibly say...
title: Earth Day

comment: Just music and light chat today. Selection is...bizarre! D'n'B, rock, 8-bit, trance, pop reggae, techno, country?! I *think* it worked though...
title: No News Is Good News, Or Something

comment: Bringing good vibes this Mental Health Week. Hear all about The Happy Newspaper, progressive and inclusive church actions, cool new politicians, and more! Plus D'n'B, hardcore, health chat, probably other stuff...
title: Mental Health Boost

comment: Spent the first ten minutes not connected and talking to myself, but from then on it's hardcore, positive news and chit-chat to get you through the day.
title: Old MacDonald Had A Rave

comment: One thing lead to another. Loads of good news - animals being awesome, people doing good, gun law reform, renewable energy, LGBTQ+ rights - and all sorts of music, including a hardcore mix (that wasn't terrible)!
title: Accidental Three Hour Mega Show (including actual mixing!)

comment: Gentle show today, for a nice mental reset. Good news about generous deeds, reforesting, overcoming racism in the KKK; and the soothing sounds of trance, breaks, piano house and ambient chill-out.
title: Little Fluffy Clouds

comment: Big catch up on good news stories, and a personal reminder to drive carefully, to a musical backdrop of some hardcore, drum and bass, ska, and old house. (I do eventually remember to turn the mic on!)
title: Remember The Good That People Do

comment: Lots of lovely animals stories and RAD music from a few punky favs, as is my recent re-obsession with Green Day!
title: Green Phase

comment: Kicking off Pride Month with an excellent piece from Pride Punx about their efforts to include the punk scene in the gay community. Apologies for the shambolic nature of the show, I was away from home and the set up was chaos! A few good news stories and tunes too :)
title: Pride Punx

comment: I didn't take any notes, so I'm not sure exactly what happened, but expect good news stories and good tunes. The cable issue is sorted early on!
title: Floorcast

comment: Triple J, DJ Shadow, Cyantific, NOFX, Mouse Rat, Green Day - so quite a variety today! Lovely stories of wheelchairs for dog, new shells for marine life, Pokemon cards paying vets bills, and more :)
title: We All Fell In The Pit

comment: Show 100 on the app. We've got UK Upfront, and breakbeat hardcore, and Sonic swings by with a musical treat for us! Great heart-warming stories about medical science, uniform equality, endangered animal births, and a gorgeous story of strangers supporting a teen coming out, and more.
title: Gonna Fly Now

comment: Lively show today, full of positive energy and silliness. Heart-warming stories of kindness and acceptance, and a wicked soundtrack of all sorts!  \n\nP.S. You might need some tissues when you hear about Philip!
title: Having A Whale Of A Time!

comment: Philanthropy, donations, nice stuff.  Music too, of course.
title: Itty Bitty Kitty Committee

comment: We settle this debate, as well as hearing about a town that bought a house for refugees, boys smashing period taboos, Mr Waddles the duck, and something about diamonds.  Musically we have ska, dnb, rock, old school hardcore to name but a few.
title: Octopus vs octopi vs octopo

comment: Today we've Alias 8 in the studio, as we chat music and nonsense, and showcase their new ambient chillout album, Digital Cinema Sound.
title: Alias 8

comment: Just music and ramblings today, as the show begins in the Positives Playlist and extends into a 90s rock-a-thon and request show,
title: Pretty much a 90s rock throwback sesh

comment: Disastrous show of tech issues, mic problems and general equipment chaos.  Not my finest hour, I get quite pissed off. Many swearings.
title: Gambles in the Shambles

comment: Sorry about the sound issues, it does level out.  Good news of dogs, giraffes, fake rain, top marketing and standing up to the lies in parliament.  Old school house, hardcore, dnb and a dash of Green Day to close.
title: Fake Rain

comment: Music equipment won't work, so its (nearly) an hour of GOOD NEWS and progressive delirium from talking constantly!
title: Blah Blah Talking Talking

comment: We have music!  Mysteriously works again, so we've a bit of everything (Green Day, Metallica mash up, lush trance, feel-good DnB) and selection of lovely stories of good news :)
title: All hail, the music returnth!

comment: Glimmers of good that have come about from the tragedy unfolding in Afghanistan, and other bits of heart-warming news.  Music flits around trance, drum and bass, hardcore, and the mighty Rant & Crazies by Luna-c.\n\n
title: Rants & Crazies

comment: Special guest Alias8 talks us through their new ambient chillout album, Digital Cinema Sound, and we talk nonsense, good news and dolphins.
title: Alias8

comment: My festival fail shenanigans.  Music from NOFX, Spunge, High Contrast, The Shamen, Luna-c, C@t in the H@t, Green Day - so all sorts!  Good news of separated conjoined twins, mental health news, human rights, and having a bee as a friend.
title: Slam Dunk The Funk

comment: Basically just talking about caterpillars!  Plus old skool breakbeat hardcore, some random indie rock tune, dash of Disney, dnb, a new one from Green Day, and finish on a old timesy classic, with a selection of good news and good deeds.\n
title: If Cyberdog Made Caterpillars

comment: Dog rescues bird, cyclists welcome refugees, coral recovery, make-up free beauty pageant - we're delving into it all!  Bit of dnb, hardcore, punk, breaks, and an ultimate final tune!
title: Radio: Not For Your Eyes, For Your Ears

comment: Dogs being awesome, child finding precious dinosaur fossil, energy company being nice, peppered with happy hardcore, breakbeat hardcore, punk and Toy Story remix and an absolute classic to close
title: Definitely Dogs, Music, Cats, Other Animals, Definitely Humans

comment: Music from Green Day, Groove Armada, Cyantific, High Contrast, Quest; and good news of camels, water supply, t-shirts, banana leaves, metal-eating bacteria and an big update on endanger animal births :)
title: Would it be good to be seal?...and other curious thoughts

comment: Threshold.fm's 3rd birthday!  Weird start, with a jolly piece of classical, then on to electro swing'n'bsss, trance, hard dnb, and a dollop or two of hardcore. Hear about a cat I met, making the best of a baby switch up, thought to speech technology, an American enjoying English phrases, paid wellbeing week, a family village, CBBC presenter diversity, a power(washer) ranger erasing hate, and rounding off with some sage words from Mr Marc Rebillet
title: A Right Ol' Rigadoon

comment: Minus the initial 8 mins of silence I broadcast, although I do forget to turn the mic on again later (sorry about that!) - stick with it, I'll be back! Ha! So 50 mins of waffle and good news today, inc alternative birth control methods and carbon suckers; and music-wise, bit of old school hardcore, Foo Fighters and Ghostbusters (?!), Chemical Brothers, 'first mix' trance tune from recent wedding, and closing off with a dash of a lovely Nintendo cover goodness.
title: What If Superman Took His Glasses Off?

comment: From a Postmodern Jukebox cover, we slip into a session of 90s rocky gems, from NOFX, Incubus, Alien Ant Farm, My Vitriol.  We discuss closed loop masks, animals being ace (as usual), and a LOT of waffle.
title: 90s Rockathon

comment: Hear all about 1EURO homes, electric cars, cooling road surfaces, and progress in trans inclusion in politics, chat registers in shops. Dancey show this time, with various Kniteforce and hardcore bits, beautiful dnb from Etherwood and High Contrast.
title: Dancey Niceland

comment: Cave rescue, duck in NY marathon, covid-19 treatments, US nappies, strangers pay remaining credit for families, cancer prevention, worker's right to sit, Waddles the duck's 3D printed leg...and a small section of silence.\nMusic: happy hardcore, Foxboro Hottubs, Subliminal Cuts
title: We'll Never Know About The Wuzzles

comment: Bumble bee without wings befriends human, Thanksgiving accidental friends meet for the 6th year, rhino poachers being scuppered by dogs, tree buildings, \nDance music from Luna-c, Aphrodite, Robert Miles and other music from The Network, Zebrahead, Less Than Jake, a request, and rounding off with some cheery happy hardcore :)\n
title: Jen Doesn't Like The Whoa-oa-oas (SYKE! I do)

comment: Picking up where we left off, with Force and Styles 'Follow Me', setting the tone as we have a joyful romp through other mid-90s - and beyond - happy hardcore classics!  Chat about Alzheimer's treatment advances, washing machines, and other stuff. Sorry about the volume levels 😬
title: Name That Tune! Happy Hardcore Edition

comment: Not a bad way to make an entrance. Not bad at all.
